ce:section.ce:para:
Liu et al. [189] synthesized yellow-green luminescent carbon quantum dots (YG-CQDs) from p-PD and CA using a straightforward one-step hydrothermal method aimed at detecting Congo Red dye. At a pH of 5, Congo Red generated polar groups (R–SO3

                           -
                        ). The abundance of carboxyl and amino functional groups on the surface of the synthesized YG-CQDs facilitated interaction with the anionic form of Congo Red, leading to the fluorescence quenching of YG-CQDs.
